        Common mistakes
      </h2>

      <div class="card card-red">
        <h3 class="card-header">The request is not actually for recorded information</h3>
        <p>FOI gives you the right to access recorded information, not to have questions answered or to receive explanations.</p>
        <p>Authorities are not obliged to create new information in response to your request</p>
      </div>
      <br>
      <div class="card card-red">
        <h3 class="card-header">Not including your name or using a fake name</h3>

        <p>For a request to be valid it needs to include your real name.</p>
      </div>
      <br>
      <div class="card card-red">
        <h3 class="card-header">Combining FOI with other issues</h3>

        <p>Don’t combine a request for information with a complaint, or general correspondence with the public authority.</p>

        <p>If you want to request your own personal information, it’s best to ask for this separately, as it is covered by different laws.</p>
      </div>
      <br>
      <div class="card card-red">
        <h3 class="card-header">Forgetting to check public information first</h3>

        <p>Where possible, it is always a good idea to see if the information that you are interested in is already published somewhere first.</p>

        <p>FOI requests take about four weeks to answer, which is a long time to wait if the information you want is already available somewhere else.</p>

        <p>If you can, we recommend searching the internet and checking the public authority’s own website before making an FOI request.</p>

        <p>See also: <a href="https://ico.org.uk/for-the-public/official-information/">https://ico.org.uk/for-the-public/official-information/</a>.</p>
      </div>

      <br>
      <div class="card card-red">
        <h3 class="card-header">Sending too many requests</h3>

        <p>If you send multiple requests for information on the same topic to an authority, they are more likely to refuse to answer them.</p>
      </div>
      <br>
      <div class="card card-red">
        <h3 class="card-header">Not specifying a format</h3>

        <p>If you would like information in a certain format, always say that format that you want the information to be in at the time of making the request.</p>

        <p>Authorities have to comply with your request if it is reasonably practicable to do so.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section-medium">
      <h2 id="request-templates">Request Templates</h2>
      <p>Here are few example requests that you can use to ask for common types of information.</p>

      <h3>Statistics</h3>
      <div class="letter">
        <p>Dear [name of council],</p>

        <p>Please provide me with a copy of the following information separately for each calendar year from 2022 to 2024:</p>

        <ol>
          <li>The number of households in the [name of council] area that were assessed as homeless.</li>
          <li>The number of households in the council area that were placed into temporary accommodation.</li>
          <li>The total expenditure by the council on temporary accommodation for homeless households.</li>
        </ol>

        <p>I would prefer to receive the response via email in Excel or CSV format.</p>

        <p>If you require any clarification, please let me know as soon as possible.</p>

        <p>Yours faithfully,</p>

        <p>[Your name]</p>
      </div>

      <h3>Documents</h3>
      <div class="letter">
        <p>Dear [authority name],</p>

        <p>Please provide me with a copy of the following information:</p>

        <ul>
          <li>[Name of report or document] produced by [authority or department]</li>
        </ul>

        <p>I would like to receive the latest version of the document in electronic format.</p>

        <p>Yours faithfully,</p>

        <p>[Your name]</p>
      </div>

      <h3>Agreements and contracts</h3>
      <div class="letter">
        <p>Dear [Authority Name],</p>
        <p>Please provide me with a copy of any contracts or agreements (formal or informal) between the [public body] and the [name of company, group or organisation] that are currently in force.</p>
        <p>Yours faithfully,<br>
        [Your name]</p>
      </div>

      <h3>Minutes of meetings</h3>
      <div class="letter">
        <p>Dear [Authority name],</p>
        <p>Please provide me with a copy of the minutes of the last two meetings of the [name of committee] for which approved minutes are available.</p>

        <p>Yours faithfully,<br>
        [Your Name]</p>
      </div>

      <h3>Consultation response</h3>
      <div class="letter">
        <p>Dear [Authority name],</p>

        <p>Please provide me with a copy of the response from [name of company/organisation] to the consultation on [subject matter] in [year].</p>

        <p>Yours faithfully,<br>
        [Your name]</p>
      </div>

      <h3>Correspondence</h3>
      <div class="letter">
        <p>Dear [Authority name],</p>

        <p>Please provide me with a copy of all correspondence between the [name of public body] and [name of company, group or organisation], its agents and representatives about [subject] during the last three months.</p>

        <p>Yours faithfully,<br>
        [Your Name]</p>
      </div>
    </section>

